This paper deals with unsupervised spoken term detection using acoustic patterns, which is a topic related to natural language processing and speech recognition. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques for pattern recognition, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of multiple sets of patterns with varying model granularity, which could be related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
